Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.70,0:11:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it must be hard to believe!{/I can't believe it myself}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.73,0:11:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you also making up impossible excuses?{/why are you saying things that don't make sense - unsure, lit is "what are you saying things that I don't understand reasons/circumstances for?"} {Yume: Enough with your nonsense!}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.17,0:11:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If you fool around, \Njust admit it and apologize!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.71,0:11:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I let my guard down with that one,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.42,0:11:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,but as a 3rd dan in karate, 4th dan in judo \Nand 3rd dan in kendo, I won't let you land{/connect} a single blow{/stroke} more.{unsure, deepl makes it Even though I've shown an opening, I'm a 3rd dan in karate, a 4th dan in judo and a 3rd dan in kendo, and I'm going to take a swing at you. but 隙を見せたとはいえ空手３段柔道４段に剣道３段の私に一撃を加えると seems to be "this one blow inflict damage/count in/add/sum up" so I think she means "don't get used to it"}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.05,0:11:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheeky child...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.18,0:11:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,This time, it's Ijigawa Kick!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.31,0:11:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.67,0:11:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,While putting on a face of docility, \Nyour true intent has been a rebellion against teacher?!{lit: I thought you have a quiet face, yet you've had a grudge against teacher for a long time}{/Have you been truly intending to rebel against your teacher with a face of docility?!}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.07,0:11:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You're mistaken, teacher!{/it's not like that}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.98,0:11:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever it is, I must come up with some explanation.{/I don't know what is going on, but either way, it seems I have no choice but to keep lying/deceive/misrepresent/talk my way out - unsure what is buttoiukoto}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.24,0:11:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, what's all that dancing about?{/what is the meaning of this dance}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.37,0:11:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I figured I could show you \Nthis thinking dance of mine.{/I thought to let you see my dance for better thinking }
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.73,0:11:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Dancing, dancing, dancing!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.55,0:12:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Hop,{/jump/dance} hop, hop, and twist{/screw}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.18,0:12:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you say? \NIsn't that cool?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.76,0:12:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Honmaru! Let me too! Me too!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.60,0:12:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Ijigawa-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.92,0:12:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now go for the boobs!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.27,0:12:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Squeeze, squeeze, squeeze, squeeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.09,0:12:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I help too, like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.20,0:12:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the meaning of this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.31,0:12:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Rui-chan...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.97,0:13:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Taruruuto, we didn't go a bit too far \Nwith this one, did we?{/overdo it}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.28,0:13:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Saw it? Saw it? Saw it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.56,0:13:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You get it now? \NNo teacher is a match for me!{/I'm not afraid of no teacher/not even teacher is worthy opponent for me}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.48,0:13:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like your daily humiliation has been avenged!{unsure, lit is "usual/habutual everyone's grudge has been cleansed/refreshed/dispelled, I feel grateful" also deepl makes it neat "I'll make it up to you guys for all the shit you've been through. You should be grateful." which is probably the truth}\NHow about thanking me, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.37,0:13:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Turns out, we didn't go far enough, Taru.{/we didn't overdo it at all}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.18,0:13:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheer up, Honmaru! \NOur pranks on Ijigawa are off to a good start!{I've no clue why he says "mischief with ijigawa has started" I think he implies we'll keep doing this, unlike in manga}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.71,0:13:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Iyona-chan despises me nevertheless!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.28,0:14:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Why am I, as a man, so unfortunate?{I really hope it's fukouna - unhappiness; sorrow; misfortune; disaster; accident}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.05,0:14:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,All my trials and tribulations arise because of just one girl, \Nthe meanest in all of Japan!{lit: this and that, is all the fault of #1 super-malicious woman in japan}{maybe most dastardly would work better, but overall, I'm very unsure about the right word for ijiwaru here, which is to act vicious/as a villain}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.02,0:14:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time you're playing meanie on me, \Nyou're not getting away with it, Ijigawa Rui!{/this time if you dare to act dastardly towards me, I'm not stopping at just that/not leaving it be}{I'd like to find some english word here sounding close enough to reflect ijigawa's name literally meaning "meanie" but the closest I could get is "cRUel/RUde"}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.96,0:14:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Honmaru-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.52,0:14:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Iyona-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.46,0:14:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Rui-chan is not as bad a girl as you think.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.69,0:14:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But still...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.78,0:14:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I really like Rui-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.43,0:14:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why we're friends.{/we're friends, after all}
